7. Non-Clinical and Non-Diagnostic Boundary

This repository is research-stage, non-clinical, non-diagnostic, non-therapeutic, non-surveillance, non-coercive, pre-device, pre-certification, and pre-compliance.

Materials in this repository must not be used to claim:

- diagnosis
- treatment
- disease monitoring
- prevention
- clinical decision support
- psychiatric scoring
- medical stress scoring
- consciousness truth scoring
- psychological safety scoring
- employment ranking
- insurance ranking
- educational ranking
- legal eligibility assessment
- human surveillance scoring
- validated Sal-Meter performance
- CAIS compliance

Human-State Cost, if referenced, is a non-diagnostic benchmark construct for comparing interaction conditions.

It is not a score for ranking, diagnosing, classifying, or governing human beings.

---

8. Raw Human Data Boundary

No raw human data is licensed or published through this repository.

This repository is not a place to publish:

- raw human biosignals
- identifiable participant data
- raw video from real human sessions
- raw audio from real human sessions
- face data
- private session logs
- clinical records
- consent forms containing personal information
- internal lab packages
- unpublished human-subject files

Public examples should use only:

- synthetic data
- toy data
- mock data
- schema-only examples
- non-identifying demonstration files

---

9. Repository Role

This repository exists to demonstrate how the SICS Human-State Proxy Benchmark Track boundary can become technical helper structure.

It may support:

- synchronized multimodal benchmark design
- metadata discipline
- leakage-safe evaluation
- synthetic/sample data structure
- baseline model skeletons
- dashboard mockups
- closed-loop demo-lite planning
- future comparison with Sal-Meter I/G-channel inputs

It does not define CAIS.

It does not define Sal-Meter.

It does not validate Sal-Meter.

It does not publish raw human data.

It does not replace DOI-registered SICS / CAIS / Sal-Meter / CCF records.

---

10. Final Boundary Sentence

Proxy first as benchmark.

Sal-Meter later as core input.

Claims never ahead of evidence.

This repository exists to prepare the comparison layer without confusing it with the molecular-electrochemical Sal-Meter core.
